Reasoning: The paper discusses the design of systems and tools to support data preservation and reproducibility in scientific research, specifically in the field of High Energy Physics. This involves considerations of user attitudes towards communication, collaboration, and automation, as well as scalability challenges. Based on these topics, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), followed by Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Databases (cs.DB), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Software Engineering (cs.SE).
